time ./anagrams  > /dev/null

All times are on the dell optiplex, unless otherwise noted.

For testing a new implementation, note that the words file should wind
up with 72717 words (66890 distinct bags), and after pruning for
"Ernest Hemingway", it should have 1716 entries.  Unfortunately that
file seems to exist in different versions on different *nix distros,
which is why I've checked in my own copy.  I suspect that many of the
implementations here that got the wrong answer did so not because
they're buggy, but only because I unknowingly tested them against a
different version of the dictionary than the Common Lisp version.

Also note that the times are meaningless if the answer isn't correct.
For example, if the answer contains too few items, then the time will
be notably lower than if the answer were correct.

"Correct answer" basically means "did it get the same results as the Common Lisp version?"

